; native-content-address-band.fk — the Python-free write path's core property,
; witnessed on the c-bootstrap fkwu (--src).
;
; WHY THIS EXISTS: the Python carrier's public write lane wedged three times on
; 2026-07-02, each time on `UPDATE substrate_nodes SET count = count + 1` — a
; row lock held inside a long transaction. That `count` is carrier bookkeeping;
; it is NOT part of the content-addressed identity (the NodeID is a function of
; the serialized shape). Native content-addressed interning has no such counter:
; interning the SAME content returns the SAME node with ZERO writes. So the
; wedge is a Python artifact, absent from the native primitive by construction —
; "do it without Python" does not port the wedge carefully, it dissolves it.
;
; This band witnesses that property directly and deterministically (pure, no fs,
; four-way-able): leaf content-addressing is idempotent (same -> same node, no
; counter), distinct content is distinct, and the value observes back.
;
; The fs-store half (content-keyed put/get, idempotent re-store, no mutation)
; is witnessed on --src too but needs a writable temp dir, so it lives in the
; receipt (2026-07-02-native-write-path-floor.md) rather than this pure band.
;
; HONEST FLOOR (--src lane; the full store runs on the flatten/four-way lane):
;   1. composite intern_node does NOT dedup on --src (node_eq of two identical
;      MS-PAIR composites reads 0). Leaf dedup works; composite is flatten-lane.
;   2. rem / int_to_str are not exposed on --src (blocks pure-Form hash keys).
;   3. string-buffer aliasing: mixing intern/node primitives with fs + defn in a
;      single reduction corrupts str_eq — so the leaf and fs witnesses are kept
;      in separate reductions on purpose.
;
; Witness: 7.

(do
    (defn native-content-address-band ()
        (add (add
            ; same content -> same node: idempotent, no counter, no write
            (if (node_eq (intern_trivial_int 5) (intern_trivial_int 5)) 1 0)
            ; distinct content -> distinct node
            (if (node_eq (intern_trivial_int 5) (intern_trivial_int 6)) 0 2))
            ; observation reads the leaf value back through the door
            (if (eq (node_value (intern_trivial_int 42)) 42) 4 0)))
    0)
